Value Status:
Undervalued ​(a good deal!):Price to Fair Value ratio is less than 1.0;
Near Fair Value​ (at least it's a fair price):Price to Fair Value ratio is between 1.0 and 2.0;
Overvalued ​(trading at a premium):Price to Fair Value ratio is greater than 2.0;

Rate of Return(Estimate):
Our Rate of Return Estimate represents the projected average annual return you might expect after purchasing shares in the company and holding them over the default time horizon of 5 years, based on the EPS growth rate that we have projected.

1 Securities include A shares, excluding preferred stocks, funds, bonds; 
2 pledge quantity is calculated as off-site pledge registration and Stock pledged repo ; 
3 pledge proportion calculation formula is: (quantity of off-site pledge registered + quantity of stock pledged repo transactions) / total share capital of all A-shares ; 
4 Data is based on the last trading day of the week. Data Source: CSDC, update on the last trading day of the week.
